  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best Laptop Stand for Desk 2026</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated June 2026 · Evaluated 8+ models</div>

      <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</a></li>
          <li><a href="#ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</a></li>
          <li><a href="#quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-overall">Best Overall</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-budget">Best Budget</a></li>
          <li><a href="#buying-guide">Buying Guide</a></li>
          <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <p>Putting your laptop flat on the desk is the fastest way to ruin your neck and overheat your machine. A simple aluminum stand fixes both problems for less than the cost of a dinner — it raises the screen to eye level so your spine straightens, and it lifts the chassis off the desk so the laptop can actually breathe. We evaluated eight adjustable stands based on their specifications and design features to find which ones combine ergonomic lift with real cooling benefit without wobbling under a heavy laptop.</p>

      <h2 id="how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 8 laptop stand models based on product documentation, specifications, feature analysis, and pricing comparison. Our evaluation methodology follows the <a href="/how-we-test/">ToolStep review protocol</a>, analyzing product documentation, specifications, features, and pricing. Each product was assessed across identical criteria to ensure fair comparison.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each product on four criteria: Performance (30%), Build Quality (25%), Value (20%), and Ease of Use (25%). Scores were compiled from specification analysis and feature evaluation, not marketing claims. For thermal performance we assessed stand design, material properties (aluminum vs plastic), and airflow characteristics based on manufacturer documentation. For stability we evaluated material rigidity, weight capacity ratings, and hinge specifications. For ergonomic fit we assessed height adjustment range based on published specifications and compatibility with eye-level positioning requirements.</p>

      <h2 id="ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>Our rankings are based on weighted scoring across four dimensions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance (30%)</strong> — Cooling effect and ergonomic height range</li>
        <li><strong>Build Quality (25%)</strong> — Material rigidity, weight capacity, and hinge durability</li>
        <li><strong>Value (20%)</strong> — Price-to-performance ratio compared to alternatives</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of Use (25%)</strong> — Adjustment, folding, and laptop compatibility</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Product</th>
            <th>Best For</th>
            <th>Price</th>
            <th>Rating</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Adjustable Aluminum Laptop Stand</strong></td>
            <td>Best Overall</td>
            <td>$28</td>
            <td>4.6/5</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Roost Laptop Stand v3</td>
